# Bookshelf App — Architecture Plan

## Overview
Full-stack Rust web app: Axum backend + Leptos CSR frontend + SQLite.
Manage a personal bookshelf with books, authors, search/filter, and stats.

## Workspace Structure
```
Cargo.toml              # workspace: backend, frontend, types
backend/
  Cargo.toml
  src/
    main.rs             # Axum startup, router, static file serving (0.0.0.0:8080)
    db.rs               # SQLite pool init + auto-migration
    models.rs           # sqlx::FromRow row types
    routes/
      mod.rs
      authors.rs        # /api/authors CRUD
      books.rs          # /api/books CRUD + stats + search/filter
      health.rs         # GET /health
  migrations/
    YYYYMMDD_init.sql   # CREATE TABLE authors, books
frontend/
  Cargo.toml
  Trunk.toml            # proxy /api -> 127.0.0.1:8080
  index.html            # SPA entry, meta tags, favicon
  src/
    main.rs             # mount app
    app.rs              # router + app shell + nav
    pages/
      mod.rs
      books_list.rs     # grid/cards, search bar, genre filter, sort
      book_detail.rs    # full info, edit/delete buttons
      book_form.rs      # add/edit form with author dropdown, rating stars
      authors_list.rs   # name, bio preview, book count
      author_detail.rs  # full info + books list
      author_form.rs    # add/edit author form
      stats.rs          # dashboard: totals, avg rating, genre breakdown, top-rated
      not_found.rs      # 404 page
    components/
      mod.rs
      loading.rs        # spinner
      error.rs          # error message display
      toast.rs          # toast notifications
      confirm.rs        # confirm-before-delete modal
      rating.rs         # star rating display/input
types/
  Cargo.toml
  src/lib.rs            # Book, Author, CreateBook, UpdateBook, CreateAuthor, UpdateAuthor, BookStats, etc.
```

## Key Dependencies
- **backend**: axum, tokio, sqlx (sqlite, runtime-tokio), tower-http (cors, serve-dir, trace), serde, serde_json
- **frontend**: leptos 0.7+ (csr), leptos_router, gloo-net, serde, serde_json, web-sys
- **types**: serde + serde_derive only (no framework deps, shared by both sides)

## Database Schema (SQLite via sqlx)
```sql
CREATE TABLE authors (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    name TEXT NOT NULL,
    bio TEXT,
    created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))
);

CREATE TABLE books (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    title TEXT NOT NULL,
    author_id INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES authors(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    isbn TEXT UNIQUE,
    published_year INTEGER,
    genre TEXT,
    rating INTEGER CHECK (rating >= 0 AND rating <= 5),
    cover_url TEXT,
    description TEXT,
    created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))
);
```

## API Endpoints
| Method | Path              | Notes                          |
|--------|-------------------|--------------------------------|
| GET    | /health           | Returns 200 OK                 |
| GET    | /api/authors      | List all authors               |
| POST   | /api/authors      | Create author                  |
| GET    | /api/authors/:id  | Author detail + their books    |
| PUT    | /api/authors/:id  | Update author                  |
| DELETE | /api/authors/:id  | Delete author (cascades books) |
| GET    | /api/books        | List + ?search&genre&sort      |
| POST   | /api/books        | Create book (validate fields)  |
| GET    | /api/books/:id    | Book detail                    |
| PUT    | /api/books/:id    | Update book                    |
| DELETE | /api/books/:id    | Delete book                    |
| GET    | /api/books/stats  | Aggregated statistics          |

## Frontend Routes
| Path            | Page             |
|-----------------|------------------|
| /               | Books list       |
| /books/:id      | Book detail      |
| /add-book       | Add book form    |
| /authors        | Authors list     |
| /authors/:id    | Author detail    |
| /add-author     | Add author form  |
| /stats          | Stats dashboard  |

## Issue Build Order & Dependencies
1. **#3** Init workspace — Cargo workspace, Axum hello, Leptos hello, Trunk proxy (FOUNDATION)
2. **#4** DB schema — sqlx migrations, pool setup, auto-migrate on startup
3. **#5** Authors CRUD API — depends on #4 (schema must exist)
4. **#6** Books CRUD API — depends on #5 (authors FK, similar patterns)
5. **#7** Frontend shell — app layout, nav bar, client-side routing
6. **#8** Books list page — depends on #6 (books API) + #7 (shell)
7. **#9** Book detail/form — depends on #8 (navigates from list)
8. **#10** Authors pages — depends on #5 (authors API) + #7 (shell)
9. **#11** Stats dashboard — depends on #6 (/api/books/stats)
10. **#12** Error handling/loading — polish pass across all pages
11. **#13** CORS, logging, health — backend infra polish
12. **#14** Integration tests — all APIs must be complete
13. **#15** README — last, documents everything

## Design Decisions
- **CSR-only Leptos**: Trunk builds a static SPA; backend is a pure JSON API + static file server. No SSR complexity.
- **Shared types crate**: single source of truth for request/response structs, used by both backend and frontend.
- **SQLite file DB**: default `sqlite:bookshelf.db?mode=rwc` via DATABASE_URL env var. No external services needed.
- **Trunk proxy**: during dev, Trunk on :8081 proxies /api to backend on :8080. In prod, backend serves frontend/dist via ServeDir.
- **tower-http middleware**: CORS (permissive for dev), request tracing, static file serving — all via tower layers.
